title: Chunk 1
content:
Congratulations! We are pleased to inform you that you have been shortlisted for the next step in our 
selection process for the JavaScript Development Internship position at Pianalytix. Video Assignment Details: 
 
Objective: To assess your technical skills, creativity, and ability to communicate effectively through a video 
tutorial. Video Content: 
● Introduce yourself. ● Highlight the skills you possess, particularly in JavaScript and related technologies. ● Describe a project you have built using JavaScript. ● Explain an important technique or concept related to the project in a simple and clear manner. Guidelines: 
● Duration: The video should be concise, ideally around 2-5 minutes. ● Format: Present your slides on your computer screen and record the presentation. It’s recommended to 
have your webcam on to record your face, although it’s optional.

title: Chunk 2
content:
Use any presentation tools (e.g., slides, 
code editors, screen recordings) that can effectively demonstrate your skills and project. Make sure to 
capture both the screen and your webcam feed in the recording. Save the video in MP4 format. ● Deadline: Please note that the priority deadline for submission is 3 days from the moment you receive 
it. However, the form will remain open for submissions until we finalize the applicants. We encourage 
you to submit as early as possible to increase your chances of consideration. ● Sample:This is a sample video to give you an idea of what you'll be doing in this internship: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_GuV6Db0M1U&ab_channel=PianalytiX 
● How to submit? Please compress the video to below 100 MB and upload the file directly in the 
provided Google Form. [https://forms.gle/MWxMzN7uorSrBv3R9] 
 
If your submission aligns with our expectations, we will contact you for the online interview in two or more 
weeks.
